plate><target>convert</target><arg>874</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template><space/>electrified) (2006)</paragraph><list type='bullet'><listitem>City with<space/><link><target>rapid transit</target><part>underground</part></link><space/>railway system:<space/><link><target>Minsk</target></link>, see<space/><link><target>Minsk Metro</target></link></listitem><listitem>For tramway systems: see<space/><link><target>List of town tramway systems in Belarus</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='2'>Highways</heading><paragraph><template><target>main</target><arg>Roads in Belarus</arg></template></paragraph><paragraph>The owners of highways may be the Republic of Belarus, its<space/><link><target>Administrative divisions of Belarus</target><part>political subdivisions</part></link>, legal and natural persons, who own roads, as well as legal entities, which roads are fixed on the basis of economic or operational management.</paragraph><paragraph>Republican state administration in the field of roads and road activity is the Department<space/><link><target>Belavtodor</target></link><space/>under the Ministry of Transport and Communications of the Republic of Belarus.</paragraph><paragraph>In total, in Belarus there are more than<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>93,000</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg><arg>mi</arg><arg name="sigfig">3</arg></template><space/>of roads and<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>200</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg><arg>mi</arg><arg name="sigfig">2</arg></template><space/>of departmental thousand (agriculture, industry, forestry, etc.), including<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>10000</arg><arg>mi</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="sigfig">2</arg><arg name="order">flip</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template><space/>in cities and towns. The density of paved roads has been relatively low &amp;ndash; 337&amp;nbsp;km per 1,000&amp;nbsp;km<xhtml:sup>2</xhtml:sup><space/>territory &amp;ndash; for comparison, in European countries with well-developed road network, the figure is an average of<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>906</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template>.</paragraph><paragraph><italics>total:</italics><template><target>convert</target><arg>93,055</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template><xhtml:br></xhtml:br><italics>paved:</italics><template><target>convert</target><arg>93,055</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template><space/>(2003)</paragraph><heading level='2'>Waterways</heading><paragraph><template><target>convert</target><arg>2,500</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg><arg>mi</arg><arg name="sigfig">3</arg></template><space/>(use limited by location on perimeter of country and by shallowness) (2003)<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><italics>country comparison to the world:</italics><space/>37</paragraph><heading level='2'>Pipelines</heading><paragraph>gas<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>5,250</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template>; oil<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>1,528</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template>; refined products<space/><template><target>convert</target><arg>1,730</arg><arg>km</arg><arg name="abbr">on</arg></template><space/>(2008)</paragraph><heading level='2'>Ports and harbors</heading><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Mazyr</target></link><space/>- on the river<space/><link><target>Pripyat River</target><part>Pripyat</part></link></listitem></list><heading level='2'>Airports</heading><paragraph>65 (2008):<xhtml:br></xhtml:br><italics>country comparison to the world:</italics><space/>76</paragraph><list type='bullet'><listitem><link><target>Minsk International Airport</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Minsk-1</target></link></listitem><listitem><link><target>Gomel Airport</target></link></listitem></list><heading level='3'>Airports - with paved runways</heading><paragraph><te